# .claudeignore — paths an AI agent should never read in this repo.
#
# NOTE ON EFFECTIVENESS: Claude Code's search/read tools already honor
# .gitignore, and the strongest enforcement is `permissions.deny` in
# .claude/settings.json. This file documents intent and is forward-compatible;
# the patterns below are also mirrored in .gitignore / settings where it counts.
# It is NOT a guaranteed hard block on its own — treat it as guidance.

# Dependencies (163 MB) — never read source here
node_modules/

# Build / generated output
dist/
build/
bundle-stats.html

# Lockfiles — huge, no architectural signal
package-lock.json

# Binary / media assets — cost tokens, give no code signal
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.svg
*.webm
*.mp4
public/

# Tooling / scratch artifacts (not product code)
.superpowers/
.gstack/
.vscode/
*.patch
*.pid

# Historical planning docs — read only for archaeology, not normal tasks
docs/superpowers/

# OS / logs
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
